BERLIN &#8211; The Organisation for Economic Co-operation and Development (OECD) and the African Development Bank (AfDB) expect economic growth in Africa to pick up this year and next.Presenting their latest forecasts at the sidelines of a G20 Africa summit in Berlin, both organisations forecast gross domestic product (GDP) to expand by 3.4% this year after 2.2% in the previous year.For 2018, OECD and AfDB expect the upturn to gain further momentum with a predicted expansion rate of 4.3%.